#: src/SUMMARY.md:36
msgid "Asterinas OSTD"
msgstr "Asterinas OSTD"

#: src/ostd/index.md:3
msgid ""
"Confucious remarked, \"I could follow whatever my heart desired without "
"transgressing the law.\""
msgstr ""

#: src/ostd/index.md:7
msgid "子曰： \"从心所欲，不逾矩。\""
msgstr ""

#: src/ostd/index.md:10
msgid ""
"With the Asterinas OSTD (Operating System Standard Library), you don't have "
"to learn the dark art of unsafe Rust programming and risk shooting yourself "
"in the foot. You will be doing whatever your heart desires, and be confident "
"that your kernel will never crash or be hacked due to undefined behaviors, "
"even if today marks your Day 1 as a Rust programmer."
msgstr ""
"借助 Asterinas OSTD（操作系统标准库），您无需钻研 unsafe Rust 编程的艰深技"
"艺，也不必承担误操作的风险。\n"
"您将能随心所欲地开发，并确信您的内核绝不会因未定义行为而崩溃或被攻击，即便今"
"天是您作为 Rust 程序员的第 1 天。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:18
msgid "APIs"
msgstr ""

#: src/ostd/index.md:20
msgid ""
"Asterinas OSTD stands as a powerful and solid foundation for safe kernel "
"development, providing high-level safe Rust APIs that are"
msgstr ""
"Asterinas OSTD 为安全内核开发提供了强大而坚实的基础，它提供的高层安全 Rust "
"API 是"

#: src/ostd/index.md:24
msgid "Essential for OS development, and"
msgstr "操作系统开发所必需的，并且"

#: src/ostd/index.md:25
msgid "Dependent on the use of unsafe Rust."
msgstr "依赖于不安全 Rust 的使用。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:27
msgid "Most of these APIs fall into the following categories:"
msgstr "这些 API 大多属于以下几类："

#: src/ostd/index.md:29
msgid ""
"Memory management (e.g., allocating and accessing physical memory pages)"
msgstr "内存管理（例如，分配和访问物理内存页）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:30
msgid "Task management (e.g., context switching between kernel tasks)"
msgstr "任务管理（例如，内核任务间的上下文切换）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:31
msgid "User space (e.g., manipulating and entering the user space)"
msgstr "用户空间（例如，操作和进入用户空间）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:32
msgid "Interrupt handling (e.g., registering interrupt handlers)"
msgstr "中断处理（例如，注册中断处理程序）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:33
msgid "Timer management (e.g., registering timer handlers)"
msgstr "定时器管理（例如：注册定时器处理程序）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:34
msgid "Driver support (e.g., performing DMA and MMIO)"
msgstr "驱动程序支持（例如：执行 DMA 和 MMIO 操作）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:35
msgid "Boot support (e.g., retrieving information from the bootloader)"
msgstr "启动支持（例如：从引导加载程序获取信息）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:36
msgid "Synchronization (e.g., locking and sleeping)"
msgstr "同步机制（例如：加锁与休眠）"

#: src/ostd/index.md:38
msgid ""
"To explore how these APIs come into play, see [the example of a 100-line "
"kernel in safe Rust](a-100-line-kernel.md)."
msgstr ""
"要了解这些 API 如何发挥作用，请参阅 [用安全 Rust 编写的 100 行内核示例]"
"(a-100-line-kernel.md)。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:41
msgid ""
"The OSTD APIs have been extensively documented. You can access the "
"comprehensive API documentation by visiting the [docs.rs](https://docs.rs/"
"ostd/latest/ostd)."
msgstr ""
"OSTD 的 API 已获得详尽文档支持。您可通过访问 [docs.rs](https://docs.rs/ostd/"
"latest/ostd) 获取完整的 API 文档。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:44
msgid "Four Requirements Satisfied"
msgstr "四项要求已满足"

#: src/ostd/index.md:46
msgid ""
"In designing and implementing OSTD, we have risen to meet the challenge of "
"fulfilling [the aforementioned four criteria as demanded by the framekernel "
"architecture](../kernel/the-framekernel-architecture.md)."
msgstr ""
"在设计和实现OSTD的过程中，我们已积极应对挑战，致力于满足[framekernel 架构所要"
"求的上述四项标准](../kernel/the-framekernel-architecture.md)。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:50
msgid ""
"Expressiveness is evident through Asterinas Kernel itself, where all system "
"calls, file systems, network protocols, and device drivers (e.g., Virtio "
"drivers) have been implemented in safe Rust by leveraging OSTD."
msgstr ""
"OSTD 的表现力在 Asterinas 内核中得到了充分体现，所有系统调用、文件系统、网络"
"协议和设备驱动程序（例如 Virtio 驱动程序）均已借助 OSTD 用安全的 Rust 语言实"
"现。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:58
msgid ""
"Adopting a minimalist philosophy, OSTD has a small codebase. At its core "
"lies the `ostd` crate, currently encompassing about 10K lines of code - a "
"figure that is even smaller than those of many microkernels. As OSTD "
"evolves, its codebase will expand, albeit at a relatively slow rate in "
"comparison to the OS services layered atop it."
msgstr ""
"采用极简主义理念，OSTD的代码库规模较小。其核心是`ostd` crate，目前包含约一万"
"行代码——这一数字甚至比许多微内核的代码量还要少。随着OSTD的发展，其代码库会不"
"断扩展，但与构建在它之上的操作系统服务相比，扩展速度会相对较慢。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:68
msgid ""
"The OSTD's efficiency is measurable through the performance metrics of its "
"APIs and the system calls of Asterinas Kernel. No intrinsic limitations have "
"been identified within Rust or the framekernel architecture that could "
"hinder kernel performance."
msgstr ""
"OSTD 的高效性可通过其 API 性能指标及 Asterinas 内核系统调用的表现来衡量。目前"
"尚未发现 Rust 语言或框架内核架构中存在任何可能限制内核性能的内在约束。"

#: src/ostd/index.md:75
msgid ""
"Soundness, unlike the other three requirements, is not as easily quantified "
"or proved. While formal verification stands as the gold standard, it "
"requires considerable resources and time and is not an immediate priority. "
"As a more pragmatic approach, we will explain why the high-level design is "
"sound in the soundness analysis and rely on the many eyes of the community "
"to catch any potential flaws in the implementation."
msgstr ""
"与前三项要求不同，可靠性难以直接量化或证明。虽然形式化验证是黄金标准，但其需"
"要大量资源与时间投入，并非当前的首要任务。\n"
"作为一种更务实的方法，我们将在可靠性分析中解释高层设计为何合理，并依靠社区众"
"多参与者的共同审视来发现实现中可能存在的缺陷。"

